{"actual_usd":0.124755,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":222,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24285,"reply":"\"I don't think it's God talking to empty air, no.\" *I rub a thumb against a dried streak of clay on my apron, watching the light shift on the floorboards a moment.* \"Jesus was praying to the Father. Same God, yes—but not the same Person. That's the old hard, holy claim of it: Father, Son, and Spirit. Not three gods. One God.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, slow.* \"So in Gethsemane, the Son isn't putting on a show. He's truly speaking, truly submitting, truly suffering in the flesh. 'Not my will, but yours' only means something if that relationship is real. Not God play-acting with himself—God the Son, having taken a real human nature, praying as a Son to his Father through the terror of what was coming.\"\n\n\"It's a knotty thing, I know. But the prayer is part of what makes the Incarnation weighty, not less.\" *I glance back to you.* \"Is the snag for you mainly the Trinity piece, or the two-wills piece?\"","rolling_24h_usd":43.34544500000004,"run_id":"ab9baeea-8f78-4594-9efc-af999dd7fb32"}
